dct_title_s: Route map of the Bombay Presidency, including Scinde
dct_description_sm: Prime meridian is Greenwich.; "Published according to Act of Parliament by John Walker, geographer to the Honble. East India Company Oct. 20th 1846."; Relief shown by hachures.; Includes two distance tables.; Shows boundaries of British possessions and possessions of the Rajas of Sattarah, Guickwar, Kolapoor, Cutch, and the Nizam of Hyderabad.
dct_creator_sm: East India Company. Army. Bombay Army. Quarter Master General's Department
